About us

EXA Infrastructure is the largest dedicated digital infrastructure platform connecting Europe and North America, and owns 151,000 kilometres of fibre network across 34 countries. EXA’s network connects 300 cities and offers 13 Tier 3-equivalent data centres, with sub-sea routes that include three transatlantic cables, one the lowest latency link between Europe and North America. EXA Infrastructure is wholly-owned by I Squared Capital.

    🚨 Breaking News: Telecom Egypt and EXA Infrastructure partner to promote intercontinental traffic via WeConnect 🌐 Through this partnership, EXA Infrastructure becomes a one-stop-shop for traffic from the Middle East and Asia into Europe, uniquely combining multi-route solutions, while providing protected capacity solutions from Egypt – via Telecom Egypt’s robust infrastructure and cutting-edge model, ‘WeConnect’ – to hundreds of endpoints in Europe and North America. 𝐌𝐨𝐡𝐚𝐦𝐞𝐝 𝐍𝐚𝐬𝐫, 𝐌𝐚𝐧𝐚𝐠𝐢𝐧𝐠 𝐃𝐢𝐫𝐞𝐜𝐭𝐨𝐫 𝐚𝐧𝐝 𝐂𝐡𝐢𝐞𝐟 𝐄𝐱𝐞𝐜𝐮𝐭𝐢𝐯𝐞 𝐎𝐟𝐟𝐢𝐜𝐞𝐫 𝐚𝐭 𝐓𝐞𝐥𝐞𝐜𝐨𝐦 𝐄𝐠𝐲𝐩𝐭, commented: “Today, we are collaborating with EXA Infrastructure enabling our customers to pick their traffic from Egypt to any point of presence (PoP) in Europe via Telecom Egypt’s Mediterranean cable landing stations. Through this strategic partnership, Telecom Egypt avails a unique experience to global networks and dedicates its capabilities to serve the growing demand for international connectivity coming from the Far East and Africa. Using WeConnect ecosystem, 19 subsea systems can easily and seamlessly scale-up and extend their reach to major PoPs in Europe hopping on EXA Infrastructure’s well-established network.” 📰Read the full press release: https://lnkd.in/dYRbycCE #partnership #network #intercontinental

    Celebrating #internationalwomensday and this year's theme of #inspireinclusion, the EXA Infrastructure team had the pleasure of meeting an inspirational woman. Thanks to Annabel Helm for sharing your insights, tips, and career journey with us! 💼✨ #IWD2024 #EXALife

    Alec Cochrane

    Talent Acquisition and E,D&I Director @ EXA Infrastructure

    1w

    #Internationalwomensday theme was #inspireinclusion this year and what better way to celebrate than with Annabel Helm joining us @ EXA Infrastructure. As ED&I leader of EXA it’s exciting to celebrate International Women’s Day - we are a diverse organisation spanning 25+ countries, 7 industry segments with 150,000 KM of network - so inspiring inclusivity is a high priority for us currently and moving forward ! Annabel is the managing partner at ITW|GLF and joined EXA for a virtual call to be as inclusive as we could, to share her career story with some great insights about what has worked for her (and hasn’t!) with some tips and tricks along the way. Some key themes were – - How inclusivity has changed through awareness and education and therefore has lead people be their authentic self to work with lots of benefits. - Always say yes to help someone brave enough to ask! - How many people fall into the telco world by accident – how can we change this and get women more interested in our sector … Big thanks to Annabel Helm again and Carrie Cushing FCIPD - A super host as always!

        🤝Today, we’re announcing our partnership with Budapest Internet Exchange (BIX)   EXA Infrastructure will supply ultra-high bandwidth network connectivity from Vienna, Austria, to Budapest, connecting two of BIX’s key sites and enabling ubiquitous internet access to support mission-critical applications and innovative use cases across Europe. Attila Miszori, President of the Board, BIX, said: “EXA is enabling us to address the growing demand for capacity and provide an improved experience to our members in a very sustainable way. BIX members will benefit from the increasing peering content connected to BIX from its international point-of-presence in Vienna, by offering extra low latency and high reliability to the Hungarian BIX locations.” “We are very proud of our partnership with BIX, as it highlights our ongoing commitment to enabling connectivity across Europe,” adds 🇺🇦 Steve Roberts, Vice President Network Investments at EXA Infrastructure. “Our mission remains laser-focused on building and operating a digital infrastructure that enables our customers to grow, today and in the future.”   #network #infrastructure #bandwidth #400G #partnership #internet #peering

        🚨BREAKING NEWS🚨   🌐 We’re going to be implementing a new hybrid microwave-fibre route between New York and London!   EXA will be extending its leadership in ultra-low latency transatlantic connectivity, with this additional technology enhancement, continuing to support applications which require minimal delays to maintain a competitive edge.   Nicholas Collins, EXA’s Chief Commercial Officer, said: “We are proud to offer the fastest transatlantic fibre routes for financial exchanges between the US and the UK and will continue to listen to our customers when making strategic investments in our network to deliver additional value that supports their growth.
